headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball spent his youth “playing up” against older competition.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, Ball lead Hornets to back-to-back wins vs. Bucks

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham scored 18 of his career-high 29 points in the third quarter to help the Detroit Pistons erase a 22-point deficit and beat the Utah Jazz 126-116 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham's career-high 29 leads Pistons over Jazz 126-116

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 26 points and Jayson Tatum had 24, carrying the Boston Celtics to a 101-98 overtime victory over the Indiana Pacers on Monday night in the first of a home-and-home series between the teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, Tatum carry Celtics over Pacers 101-98 in OT

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Five nights after sending them into a frenzy with his first buzzer beater, RJ Barrett had Knicks fans chanting his name.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 31, Knicks pull away to beat Spurs 111-96

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 31 points and eight rebounds to lead the Philadelphia 76ers over the Houston Rockets 111-91 Monday night for their seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid goes over 30 again, 76ers beat Rockets 111-91

headlines.description: — Jarret Allen had 18 points and 17 rebounds, Darius Garland also had a double-double and the Cleveland Cavaliers held off the Sacramento Kings 109-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs hold off late rally, send Kings to 5th straight loss

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons had 23 points and 11 assists, and the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers took advantage of James Harden's absence for a 114-108 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: With Harden out, Trail Blazers down the Nets 114-108
